	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yeah, it's just a damn game.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's a damn game that they made, maintain, and own every facet of.<br><br>It's a game they have to keep a few hundred thousand people playing, and that means keeping it competitive and balanced.  If some people are cheating and breezing past content, then the only way that others can remain competitive is by cheating as well.  Sony seeks to avoid that.<br><br>The guild &quot;worked&quot; for the drops in the same way that a powerleveled character &quot;worked&quot; for the exp.  While the other guilds were actually WORKING on the key quest (one person getting a key = 4 groups getting in to fight Seru, plus a +16 all stats earring), these people just warped on in and killed Seru.  Imagine if you were starting to fight your way down to a MOB only to find that someone else had used a bug to warp there from ZIN and killed it before you got there?  You'd be pretty pissed, but by your current statement, nothing at all is wrong with it.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
